==English==
===Noun===
'''ut'''

# syllable formerly used in [[sol-fa]] to represent the first note of a [[major scale]].  '''Ut''' has been replaced by ''[[do]]''.

: '''Ut''' was the first word of the first line of a section of [[Scripture]], where the first word in each line was taken to use for the syllable names in [[sol-fa]].

====Etymology====
From Latin ''ut''--see below.

==Latin==
===Conjunction===
'''ut'''

# [[that]], [[so that]], in order to, in order that
